label("$A$",A,SW);
label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,N);
label("6",(C+A)/2,W);
[/asy]

The area of $\triangle ABC$ is $\frac{1}{2} AB \cdot BC$.  Since $AB = AC \sqrt{2} = 6\sqrt{2}$, we have \[\frac{1}{2}(6\sqrt{2})\cdot 6=\boxed{18\sqrt{2}}\] square centimeters.

